{"questionId":"26240170","questionHtml":"<p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math> and the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to substitute both roots to form a quadratic&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for each correct value. They may be embedded or stated explicitly.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for each correct value. They must be stated explicitly.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>⇒</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to form a valid equation to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp;using their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mfenced><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 3</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to form two valid equations in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 4</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to write <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math> in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>h</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>k</mi></math> and substitute for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>h</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>⇒</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>25</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>25</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for each correct value. They may be embedded or stated explicitly.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[3 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26240170","referenceCode":"24M.1.SL.TZ1.8d","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the value of b and the value of c.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Quadratic function"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}